WEBVTT

00:00:52.157 --> 00:00:53.157
Mom!

00:01:04.967 --> 00:01:06.797
Moon Se Guk lied,

00:01:08.867 --> 00:01:09.967
but as for me,

00:01:11.437 --> 00:01:13.037
I can cure Min Seo's illness.

00:01:13.977 --> 00:01:15.237
Every single one of them...

00:01:16.807 --> 00:01:18.147
was treated by me.

00:01:22.617 --> 00:01:24.187
You must be hungry.
Come on, let's go inside.

00:01:24.247 --> 00:01:26.117
Mom, can we make a quick stop
at the convenience store first?

00:01:26.417 --> 00:01:27.687
There's something I'm really craving.

00:01:28.217 --> 00:01:30.557
Gosh. Fine. Let's go.

00:01:31.357 --> 00:01:34.097
Excuse me?

00:01:35.527 --> 00:01:37.867
Are you Kang Sang Woo?

00:01:38.897 --> 00:01:41.297
Yes, that's me.

00:01:42.367 --> 00:01:43.367
You are?

00:01:50.507 --> 00:01:51.607
Who are you?

00:01:54.317 --> 00:01:56.117
It's just that...

00:02:01.357 --> 00:02:05.727
(The Saviorâ€™s Quagmire)

00:02:24.877 --> 00:02:26.917
(Case: Serial murders,
Guam City serial murder and desecration)

00:02:26.977 --> 00:02:30.347
(Prosecution)

00:02:42.627 --> 00:02:44.697
This is Cha Yi Yeon
from Violent Crimes Unit One.

00:02:46.197 --> 00:02:49.767
I'll cut to the chase.
We've found all the victims' bodies.

00:02:51.937 --> 00:02:56.207
But to be blunt, we didn't find them.
Lee Woo Gyeom confessed.

00:02:56.747 --> 00:02:58.947
Where did you dump the remaining victims?

00:02:59.317 --> 00:03:00.877
On the mid-slope of Mount Cheonggye,

00:03:00.877 --> 00:03:03.217
facing the river,
at the 100-meter mark.

00:03:03.717 --> 00:03:05.087
Is he trying to get a reduced sentence?

00:03:05.487 --> 00:03:08.257
Yes. He asked me about a plea bargain.

00:03:08.587 --> 00:03:10.487
I don't want a lighter sentence.

00:03:10.857 --> 00:03:12.327
I want to make a different kind of deal.

00:03:13.127 --> 00:03:17.627
To this day, the number of victims,
their identities, the body locations...

00:03:17.997 --> 00:03:20.367
He's never given a straight answer
about any of it.

00:03:20.897 --> 00:03:23.437
He's toying with us even as we speak.

00:03:24.267 --> 00:03:26.007
He has no regard for human life,

00:03:26.677 --> 00:03:28.577
He's deceiving the entire nation watching,

00:03:29.547 --> 00:03:31.607
all while looking down on us from above.

00:03:32.317 --> 00:03:35.047
So what's your point?

00:03:37.017 --> 00:03:38.917
Now it's your turn to cross the line,
Prosecutor Cha.

00:03:39.817 --> 00:03:41.317
Come over to my side.

00:03:41.617 --> 00:03:43.657
I will personally show you in court.

00:03:44.087 --> 00:03:47.357
How I can save a life
without so much as a scalpel.

00:03:48.757 --> 00:03:50.797
You crazy punk...

00:03:53.797 --> 00:03:56.207
We will be seeking the death penalty.

00:03:59.307 --> 00:04:01.537
(The Establishment of Law and Order)

00:04:05.077 --> 00:04:07.017
You seem more at ease today.

00:04:08.577 --> 00:04:10.447
I just came from seeing Sang Woo.

00:04:11.047 --> 00:04:12.517
That's just like you, Attorney Park.

00:04:13.787 --> 00:04:14.857
What do you mean? "Just like me?"

00:04:16.527 --> 00:04:17.857
You think you know me?

00:04:18.427 --> 00:04:22.727
That you're a good father
who loves Min Seo more than anything...

00:04:22.797 --> 00:04:25.997
Don't talk so casually about my daughter.

00:04:26.667 --> 00:04:28.697
Gosh, it was a compliment.
That's a little harsh.

00:04:29.567 --> 00:04:32.307
Did you really cure Sang Woo?

00:04:32.977 --> 00:04:34.107
Didn't you see him walking?

00:04:36.977 --> 00:04:39.877
That Sang Woo was cured because of you.
That's something I...

00:04:41.217 --> 00:04:42.217
How am I supposed to believe that?

00:04:43.117 --> 00:04:44.117
Good.

00:04:45.387 --> 00:04:46.987
You should keep doubting me.

00:04:47.687 --> 00:04:49.957
That's the only way
you'll want to see the real thing.

00:04:52.397 --> 00:04:53.497
Attorney Park,

00:04:55.457 --> 00:04:58.127
when people come back from the dead,

00:04:58.897 --> 00:05:01.097
they come to realize
more than what meets the eye.

00:05:02.307 --> 00:05:04.967
I was in a coma for three years
after a car accident.

00:05:13.117 --> 00:05:14.777
I had no idea how I woke up,

00:05:15.347 --> 00:05:17.847
much less why.

00:05:19.387 --> 00:05:23.257
My doctor said I had a new blood mutation,

00:05:25.697 --> 00:05:27.527
but I couldn't just take his word for it.

00:05:28.527 --> 00:05:31.097
I was just an ordinary med student
back then.

00:05:34.367 --> 00:05:36.237
But there was another problem.

00:05:38.637 --> 00:05:40.037
As an aftereffect of the accident,

00:05:41.577 --> 00:05:43.647
waves of pain would hit me out of nowhere.

00:05:48.277 --> 00:05:51.047
The exact same pain
I felt during the car crash.

00:05:57.327 --> 00:05:58.957
I couldn't find the cause.

00:06:00.897 --> 00:06:02.827
So, since I was living
on borrowed time anyway,

00:06:03.767 --> 00:06:05.527
I started experimenting on my own body.

00:06:07.867 --> 00:06:10.437
I did all sorts of crazy things,
not caring if I died.

00:06:12.267 --> 00:06:14.707
I injected myself with anything
that could possibly be a cure.

00:06:20.477 --> 00:06:21.577
But then one day,

00:06:22.687 --> 00:06:24.147
the pain was gone.

00:06:25.217 --> 00:06:27.717
I had created a cure
for an incurable disease.

00:06:28.257 --> 00:06:30.587
For the very disease that
they said was untreatable.

00:06:31.727 --> 00:06:35.457
The pain, the aftereffects of the coma...
They were all gone.

00:06:37.967 --> 00:06:41.137
You're saying you found a cure?

00:06:42.067 --> 00:06:45.977
Yes. And I realized that method
could be used to cure other diseases too.

00:06:48.837 --> 00:06:49.947
You can really...

00:06:51.007 --> 00:06:52.477
You can cure the Batten disease,
can't you?

00:07:01.557 --> 00:07:03.357
No one believed me at first.

00:07:06.627 --> 00:07:08.257
But they all survived,

00:07:09.127 --> 00:07:11.427
and every single person who woke up
was grateful to me.

00:07:14.397 --> 00:07:15.667
Life and death...

00:07:17.037 --> 00:07:18.437
It's nothing to me.

00:07:23.847 --> 00:07:25.407
(Court)

00:07:25.477 --> 00:07:28.617
- Bring back the death penalty!
- Bring it back!

00:07:28.677 --> 00:07:31.587
- Bring it back!
- Harsh punishment for violent criminals!

00:07:31.647 --> 00:07:33.787
- Punish them!
- Punish them!

00:07:33.817 --> 00:07:36.127
- That's Lee Woo Gyeom!
- Murderer! Killer!

00:07:36.227 --> 00:07:37.727
- Killer!
- Murderer!

00:07:39.057 --> 00:07:43.267
- Lee Woo Gyeom, you murderer!
- Hey, killer!

00:07:44.267 --> 00:07:47.237
- Bring back the death penalty!
- Bring it back!

00:07:47.297 --> 00:07:49.567
Following the arrest of
serial killer Lee Woo Gyeom,

00:07:49.607 --> 00:07:53.637
public support for resuming executions
has been rising dramatically.

00:07:54.037 --> 00:07:55.277
According to a recent poll,

00:07:55.277 --> 00:07:57.807
a staggering 74.3 percent
of respondents said...

00:07:57.907 --> 00:08:01.247
they were in favor of resuming executions.

00:08:01.547 --> 00:08:03.847
Meanwhile, the attorney
handling Lee Woo Gyeom's trial,

00:08:03.917 --> 00:08:07.317
Park Han Jun,
is also facing continued controversy.

00:08:07.857 --> 00:08:09.727
Attorney Park was
formerly a prosecutor for...

00:08:09.727 --> 00:08:11.027
the Central Investigation Department...

00:08:11.087 --> 00:08:13.757
before becoming a civil rights attorney.
However, in recent years...

00:08:23.767 --> 00:08:27.377
The defendant killed 17 people.
Is that correct?

00:08:27.777 --> 00:08:28.777
Yes.

00:08:29.037 --> 00:08:32.177
And you claim you killed them
while experimenting to create a cure?

00:08:32.617 --> 00:08:35.377
- Yes, that's correct.
- Assuming your claim is true,

00:08:35.917 --> 00:08:38.147
the process
in which 17 people were killed.

00:08:38.547 --> 00:08:42.287
- Where are the records of that research?
- Your Honor.

00:08:42.957 --> 00:08:48.397
The records in Exhibit 23 contain
the research on the 17 victims.

00:08:48.627 --> 00:08:49.667
Your Honor.

00:08:50.167 --> 00:08:54.067
However, the victims' bodies
are so severely mutilated...

00:08:54.197 --> 00:08:58.167
that the National Forensic Service reports
they can't confirm their identities.

00:08:59.277 --> 00:09:00.307
(Prosecution)

00:09:10.247 --> 00:09:11.247
Defendant!

00:09:12.117 --> 00:09:16.727
If your goal was research,
why dismember the victims so brutally?

00:09:16.857 --> 00:09:19.087
If your goal was truly research, then why!

00:09:19.997 --> 00:09:24.067
Why did Hong Jae Gwang have to be murdered
and left in such a wretched state?

00:09:28.837 --> 00:09:30.867
(Defendant)

00:09:33.507 --> 00:09:34.507
Your Honor.

00:09:35.177 --> 00:09:37.807
If the defendant's true intention
was research,

00:09:38.907 --> 00:09:43.387
would he have needed to desecrate
the victims' bodies to such an extent?

00:09:44.217 --> 00:09:45.217
How interesting.

00:09:45.687 --> 00:09:47.457
Therefore, we contend that this case...

00:09:48.117 --> 00:09:50.887
is just a series of thrill kills
by a psychopathic murderer.

00:09:50.957 --> 00:09:51.957
Your Honor.

00:09:53.227 --> 00:09:55.357
The prosecution's assertion
of "thrill kills" is...

00:09:55.857 --> 00:09:58.727
merely an emotional argument
with no evidence whatsoever.

00:09:59.167 --> 00:10:02.567
Sustained.
Prosecutor, do you have any grounds?

00:10:02.937 --> 00:10:05.267
Yes. I'll present them now.

00:10:07.307 --> 00:10:08.307
Defendant.

00:10:10.277 --> 00:10:11.707
You're familiar with
Jo Gyeong Chan, correct?

00:10:12.047 --> 00:10:13.047
Yes.

00:10:13.117 --> 00:10:16.917
Five years ago, you were hit by a car
driven by Jo Gyeong Chan,

00:10:17.347 --> 00:10:22.057
which left you in a coma for three years.
How did you feel about that?

00:10:22.627 --> 00:10:23.727
You must have been angry, right?

00:10:24.557 --> 00:10:28.157
Resentful that this happened to you.
And over time,

00:10:29.027 --> 00:10:31.027
towards the person responsible
for the accident,

00:10:32.067 --> 00:10:34.067
you must have felt anger
and a desire for revenge.

00:10:34.497 --> 00:10:36.567
- That's not true.
- It's not?

00:10:36.637 --> 00:10:37.637
No, it is not.

00:10:37.707 --> 00:10:40.177
Then why did you seek out
and murder Jo Gyeong Chan?

00:10:40.477 --> 00:10:41.507
Jo Gyeong Chan?

00:11:12.007 --> 00:11:14.707
Your Honor. The defendant's crimes...

00:11:15.337 --> 00:11:18.777
were premeditated murders born
from anger and a desire for revenge.

00:11:19.077 --> 00:11:22.917
He targeted adults whose disappearances
were unlikely to be investigated,

00:11:22.987 --> 00:11:26.817
making this a clear case
of calculated serial murder.

00:11:27.357 --> 00:11:29.957
I submit their traffic accident record
as evidence.

00:11:29.957 --> 00:11:32.587
The accident between the defendant
and the victim, Jo Gyeong Chan,

00:11:48.307 --> 00:11:51.207
- Look at him.
- Darn... He's a monster.

00:11:52.347 --> 00:11:53.347
Stop provoking them.

00:11:53.647 --> 00:11:55.747
I'm not provoking them. It's just absurd.

00:11:56.987 --> 00:11:59.087
- Look at him. My goodness.
- Order!

00:11:59.457 --> 00:12:01.087
I will have you removed
from the courtroom if not.

00:12:02.417 --> 00:12:04.387
(Defendant)

00:12:07.027 --> 00:12:09.127
Counsel for the defense, your rebuttal.

00:12:10.027 --> 00:12:12.737
(Defense Counsel)

00:12:13.367 --> 00:12:14.367
Your Honor.

00:12:16.507 --> 00:12:17.867
The prosecution's argument...

00:12:19.537 --> 00:12:20.737
does have some merit.

00:12:21.477 --> 00:12:25.247
And that's because you have yet to hear
the details of how my client...

00:12:25.647 --> 00:12:27.577
performed his treatments.

00:12:29.987 --> 00:12:33.387
Are you saying you can explain
the treatment process?

00:12:34.117 --> 00:12:35.217
I won't just explain it.

00:12:36.887 --> 00:12:40.097
I'll show you firsthand.

00:12:43.367 --> 00:12:47.697
I would like to call as witnesses
the six terminally ill patients...

00:12:49.437 --> 00:12:50.737
whom the defendant claims to have cured.

00:13:00.817 --> 00:13:02.017
So who are the witnesses?

00:13:04.647 --> 00:13:05.747
I still have to find them.

00:13:06.187 --> 00:13:07.187
What?

00:13:07.687 --> 00:13:09.257
So you were just bluffing?

00:13:09.927 --> 00:13:11.487
I had to shift the momentum of the trial.

00:13:11.827 --> 00:13:14.297
It was leaning in Prosecutor Cha's favor
from the start.

00:13:17.697 --> 00:13:19.967
You make it sound like it's my fault.

00:13:20.337 --> 00:13:21.567
That's because it is.

00:13:22.467 --> 00:13:25.467
Why did you have to mutilate
the bodies like that?

00:13:26.137 --> 00:13:28.677
You only call it "mutilation"
because you see it as murder.

00:13:29.647 --> 00:13:31.777
"Why are you dissecting a frog
so cruelly?"

00:13:32.107 --> 00:13:33.647
That's the exact same question.

00:13:34.047 --> 00:13:35.117
But Hong Jae Gwang was different.

00:13:35.417 --> 00:13:37.547
Because the experiment with him
was a success.

00:13:38.887 --> 00:13:41.857
So you drained all of his blood?

00:13:41.957 --> 00:13:45.527
Yes, that's when I figured out
how to create the cure.

00:13:50.827 --> 00:13:52.227
To you, when it comes to your experiments,

00:13:53.397 --> 00:13:55.067
murder is just part of the process.

00:13:58.637 --> 00:14:02.307
If Hong Jae Gwang's experiment failed,
you wouldn't have stopped at 17, right?

00:14:03.007 --> 00:14:04.407
Just be honest with me.

00:14:05.547 --> 00:14:06.647
Stop lying.

00:14:07.117 --> 00:14:09.847
- Lie about what?
- Because you wanted to kill him.

00:14:11.117 --> 00:14:12.117
That's why you killed him.

00:14:13.017 --> 00:14:16.257
That's why you killed
Jo Gyeong Chan first, isn't it?

00:14:17.627 --> 00:14:19.927
Be honest with me about your motive,

00:14:21.097 --> 00:14:25.067
and let's focus on proving your ability.
If you're caught lying in court,

00:14:25.997 --> 00:14:27.097
you won't escape the death penalty.

00:14:27.497 --> 00:14:28.667
I don't care.

00:14:29.267 --> 00:14:31.267
They won't execute me anyway.

00:14:32.137 --> 00:14:37.077
Besides, would they really execute someone
who can cure the terminally ill?

00:14:40.217 --> 00:14:41.217
That's only...

00:14:43.017 --> 00:14:45.087
if your treatment is recognized.
Only if it's recognized.

00:14:47.717 --> 00:14:48.787
That's why...

00:14:49.657 --> 00:14:52.727
I need you to get my ability recognized
through this trial.

00:14:52.827 --> 00:14:54.627
Get those witnesses to testify too.

00:14:55.697 --> 00:14:58.027
That's the only way to treat Min Seo,
right?

00:15:01.467 --> 00:15:04.107
(Hae Gang Law Firm)

00:15:10.977 --> 00:15:14.677
(Attorney Park Han Jun)

00:15:19.047 --> 00:15:20.087
Park Han Jun.

00:15:21.257 --> 00:15:22.617
Do you really have to
take the Lee Woo Gyeom case?

00:15:23.357 --> 00:15:26.027
It's not too late. Please, just drop it.

00:15:26.697 --> 00:15:28.597
I'll try to persuade the director again.

00:15:28.857 --> 00:15:29.897
It's fine.

00:15:32.497 --> 00:15:35.797
How is this fine?
You're not thinking straight.

00:15:36.197 --> 00:15:38.767
Why on earth would you agree
to defend a serial killer?

00:15:39.167 --> 00:15:40.707
If you become the public's punching bag,

00:15:41.007 --> 00:15:43.747
- what kind of client would hire you?
- I have to do this.

00:15:43.947 --> 00:15:44.947
But why?

00:15:45.777 --> 00:15:47.077
Why does it have to be you?

00:15:48.377 --> 00:15:50.387
It's a case I have to take.

00:15:51.887 --> 00:15:54.287
For Lee Woo Gyeom... And...

00:15:57.757 --> 00:15:58.857
for me.

00:16:10.807 --> 00:16:12.667
You are off the route.

00:16:22.547 --> 00:16:25.947
Reporter Jo, it's me.
My GPS can't seem to find the place.

00:16:26.757 --> 00:16:30.657
The roads around here are a real maze,
so it's hard to find.

00:16:31.027 --> 00:16:32.057
What do you see around you?

00:16:33.127 --> 00:16:34.757
Not much besides the sky,

00:16:35.457 --> 00:16:37.827
And a long flight of stairs to my right.

00:16:38.027 --> 00:16:41.867
- See the sky? Then you're almost here.
- Really?

00:16:43.837 --> 00:16:44.837
I see your car.

00:16:45.807 --> 00:16:49.107
- I see you.
- Yes. Just keep coming straight up.

00:16:50.407 --> 00:16:51.407
Right here.

00:16:55.947 --> 00:16:57.717
All right, you're parked, right?

00:16:58.987 --> 00:17:00.657
You're here, Attorney Park.

00:17:06.727 --> 00:17:08.827
Man, you must've had a hard time
getting here.

00:17:13.267 --> 00:17:16.767
Ta-da! Cozy, right?

00:17:18.367 --> 00:17:19.367
Goodness.

00:17:20.137 --> 00:17:21.177
Gosh.

00:17:25.447 --> 00:17:26.877
It feels lived in.

00:17:27.677 --> 00:17:29.277
Here, let me take that.

00:17:30.417 --> 00:17:32.187
This is your spot right here.

00:17:32.817 --> 00:17:34.717
You must be thirsty.
Instant coffee or cold water?

00:17:35.187 --> 00:17:36.317
No, I'm good.

00:17:36.757 --> 00:17:37.827
Come on, at least let me...

00:17:59.877 --> 00:18:01.347
Here, have a nice, cold glass.

00:18:02.977 --> 00:18:04.417
Don't worry, the water's clean.

00:18:10.187 --> 00:18:14.257
If six witnesses claim Lee Woo Gyeom
cured their incurable diseases,

00:18:14.327 --> 00:18:16.197
do you think the court will see
the case a little differently?

00:18:16.827 --> 00:18:18.267
They'd have to.

00:18:18.667 --> 00:18:20.737
It would completely change
the motive for the murders.

00:18:23.337 --> 00:18:24.367
Yes.

00:18:25.167 --> 00:18:26.407
Right.

00:18:27.707 --> 00:18:29.307
About Lee Woo Gyeom,

00:18:29.677 --> 00:18:31.307
I heard they're moving him
to solitary confinement.

00:18:32.547 --> 00:18:35.317
It's just a psychological tactic
to corner him.

00:18:36.417 --> 00:18:38.617
This puts us at a disadvantage
in so many ways.

00:18:42.717 --> 00:18:43.757
Reporter Jo.

00:18:44.487 --> 00:18:45.527
Yes?

00:18:48.127 --> 00:18:49.697
How about you write an article for me?

00:18:53.667 --> 00:18:56.167
(Why Prosecution Ignores the Truth?)

00:18:57.007 --> 00:18:58.437
It's a reporter named Jo Woo Cheol.

00:18:58.767 --> 00:19:01.207
He's the one who's clashed with
the financial crimes unit before.

00:19:02.007 --> 00:19:03.977
Can't you shut him up?

00:19:05.177 --> 00:19:07.247
We don't need to respond
to this kind of tabloid trash.

00:19:07.317 --> 00:19:09.347
I'm telling you.
He's working with Attorney Park.

00:19:10.247 --> 00:19:11.617
With Attorney Park Han Jun?

00:19:11.947 --> 00:19:13.987
This is exactly why I can't relax.

00:19:15.217 --> 00:19:17.087
I told you to pay attention
to every little detail.

00:19:18.127 --> 00:19:19.427
If we make one wrong move...

00:19:21.757 --> 00:19:24.327
See? It just becomes a huge pain,
understand?

00:19:27.197 --> 00:19:28.437
Yes, hello?

00:19:29.567 --> 00:19:30.807
This is Cha Yi Yeon speaking.

00:19:31.607 --> 00:19:34.737
Director Oh is unavailable at the moment,
so I'm taking his calls.

00:19:37.647 --> 00:19:39.477
Yes, he's doing well,
thank you for asking.

00:19:40.147 --> 00:19:41.147
By any chance,

00:19:41.547 --> 00:19:44.217
are you calling about that strange article
that was published today?

00:19:45.317 --> 00:19:49.957
Please don't worry, Chief Prosecutor.
I will take care of this precisely,

00:19:50.027 --> 00:19:52.027
and I'll handle it with no loose ends.

00:19:53.527 --> 00:19:56.827
Yes, of course. The director is back.
One moment, please.

00:19:57.197 --> 00:19:58.197
Here you go.

00:19:59.897 --> 00:20:01.137
"Precisely?"

00:20:02.067 --> 00:20:03.137
Don't worry.

00:20:04.037 --> 00:20:06.007
Hello, Chief Prosecutor?
This is Director Oh.

00:20:07.037 --> 00:20:08.037
Yes.

00:20:08.737 --> 00:20:09.737
Yes.

00:20:14.547 --> 00:20:15.817
Number 5896, in your cell.

00:20:30.297 --> 00:20:32.067
That's him, right? The serial killer.

00:20:32.367 --> 00:20:33.837
Look at that pretty face.

00:20:34.367 --> 00:20:38.467
- He's got killer looks.
- Hey, new guy. Don't stare like that.

00:20:38.537 --> 00:20:41.707
Lose the death stare.
Hey, what are you lookin' at?

00:20:42.677 --> 00:20:46.247
Hey, look at this bastard's face.
You killed 17 people, huh?

00:20:46.307 --> 00:20:47.847
You disrespectful punk.

00:20:48.117 --> 00:20:50.347
Get over here.
I want a good look at your face.

00:20:51.147 --> 00:20:53.457
Hey. Hey!

00:21:13.477 --> 00:21:15.377
(Jaeil Hospital)

00:21:15.437 --> 00:21:17.507
(Pediatric Ward Nurses' Station)

00:21:21.147 --> 00:21:22.147
Min Seo.

00:21:22.217 --> 00:21:25.417
Doctor, her breathing is unstable.
Her BP and pulse keep dropping too.

00:21:25.647 --> 00:21:28.287
Min Seo, look at Mommy. Min Seo!

00:21:36.457 --> 00:21:38.697
Hey. What's wrong with Min Seo?

00:21:40.137 --> 00:21:41.797
It must have been the increased dosage.

00:21:42.937 --> 00:21:45.537
She's stable for now,
but I'll run some more detailed tests.

00:21:52.207 --> 00:21:53.247
Jae Hee.

00:21:54.547 --> 00:21:55.547
Let's...

00:21:56.277 --> 00:21:57.917
Let's try to get that new drug again.

00:21:58.647 --> 00:22:00.687
That drug was only tested on adults.

00:22:00.957 --> 00:22:03.387
It could be dangerous
for children like Min Seo.

00:22:04.727 --> 00:22:05.727
But still,

00:22:06.227 --> 00:22:08.197
we can't just go through
the same thing day after day.

00:22:08.927 --> 00:22:12.467
Doing the same thing over and over
is what's keeping our Min Seo alive.

00:22:14.597 --> 00:22:15.637
Listen to me.

00:22:16.467 --> 00:22:19.107
I think about our Min Seo all the time.

00:22:30.747 --> 00:22:32.947
They said no other patient has held on
as long as our Min Seo has.

00:22:34.317 --> 00:22:36.157
We've done so well up to now,

00:22:37.657 --> 00:22:39.257
so our Min Seo will be fine.

00:22:40.297 --> 00:22:41.297
You're right.

00:22:41.997 --> 00:22:43.127
Our Min Seo...

00:22:43.797 --> 00:22:45.227
will get healthy again.

00:22:47.237 --> 00:22:48.737
And I will make sure she does.

00:22:52.907 --> 00:22:54.077
I'm sorry.

00:22:55.207 --> 00:22:56.807
Appearing in court...

00:22:57.947 --> 00:22:59.107
It's too much for me.

00:23:00.477 --> 00:23:01.547
Ma'am,

00:23:02.547 --> 00:23:03.747
we just need you to testify...

00:23:04.787 --> 00:23:06.417
that Sang Woo was treated...

00:23:07.217 --> 00:23:09.617
by Lee Woo Gyeom. That's all.

00:23:10.157 --> 00:23:11.257
My Sang Woo...

00:23:12.487 --> 00:23:13.727
Even though he's recovered,

00:23:14.427 --> 00:23:16.767
it's still not easy for him
to face the world.

00:23:17.027 --> 00:23:18.567
I don't want the whole world to know...

00:23:19.427 --> 00:23:21.037
the fact that my son was sick.

00:23:23.767 --> 00:23:27.777
If people find out he was treated
by a murderer, what will they think?

00:23:28.177 --> 00:23:29.237
I'm sorry.

00:23:30.147 --> 00:23:32.777
Wait... Ma'am!

00:23:40.587 --> 00:23:41.717
What about the patient, Oh Min Gyu?

00:23:42.857 --> 00:23:43.927
Have you reached him?

00:23:44.257 --> 00:23:48.157
His testimony is on record,
but we haven't confirmed his identity yet.

00:23:48.327 --> 00:23:53.027
Also, all six patients treated
by Lee Woo Gyeom are refusing to testify.

00:23:53.597 --> 00:23:57.207
If we want to bring them in,
we might have to subpoena them.

00:23:57.267 --> 00:24:00.107
No, absolutely not. If we do that,

00:24:01.007 --> 00:24:03.477
we might not get the testimony we need.

00:24:05.307 --> 00:24:07.717
- So, what do we do?
- We just have to keep...

00:24:08.147 --> 00:24:09.617
trying to persuade them.

00:24:15.587 --> 00:24:18.627
(Oh Min Gyu, 25 years old,
Recovered Batten disease)

00:24:18.687 --> 00:24:21.997
(True Rehabilitation)

00:24:22.057 --> 00:24:25.127
(Strive to Live Righteously)

00:24:36.207 --> 00:24:37.907
Something about that punk
just rubs me the wrong way.

00:24:39.147 --> 00:24:41.477
I heard that he killed
17 people all by himself.

00:24:41.917 --> 00:24:42.977
Seventeen people?

00:24:44.217 --> 00:24:46.647
- What crew is he with?
- He's not with any crew.

00:24:46.917 --> 00:24:48.287
They say he came up as a lone wolf.

00:24:48.987 --> 00:24:49.987
A lone wolf.

00:24:52.957 --> 00:24:53.997
Go on.

00:24:54.497 --> 00:24:55.597
Stare all you want.

00:24:56.457 --> 00:24:58.327
Once we're in the same cell,
I'll beat you senseless.

00:25:00.067 --> 00:25:02.097
- Damn it.
- You fool!

00:25:09.137 --> 00:25:12.707
(Please be quiet.)

00:25:18.017 --> 00:25:19.887
Changing the witnesses' minds...

00:25:20.617 --> 00:25:21.957
is going to take some time.

00:25:23.187 --> 00:25:24.227
How cheap.

00:25:24.627 --> 00:25:26.127
And to think they were begging me
to save them.

00:25:27.527 --> 00:25:29.497
Of all the patients you treated,

00:25:30.127 --> 00:25:31.167
by any chance,

00:25:31.827 --> 00:25:33.537
do you remember a patient
named Oh Min Gyu?

00:25:34.597 --> 00:25:36.797
Yes. The one with Batten disease.

00:25:37.467 --> 00:25:38.807
Can you get in touch with him?

00:25:39.167 --> 00:25:42.807
No.
Once their treatment is over, that's it.

00:25:44.247 --> 00:25:45.247
I see.

00:25:47.347 --> 00:25:48.747
But it must be nice to be Min Seo.

00:25:49.617 --> 00:25:51.517
Having a father who only cares about her.

00:25:51.887 --> 00:25:53.147
Focus on your case.

00:25:56.087 --> 00:25:57.087
Alright, then.

00:25:58.557 --> 00:26:02.057
Don't you have some kind of record
of how you treated them?

00:26:02.757 --> 00:26:04.727
- Of course I do.
- You do?

00:26:06.467 --> 00:26:10.097
But the witnesses have to testify
for the court to admit them as evidence.

00:26:11.007 --> 00:26:15.007
Since the witnesses can't testify now,
just submitting those records...

00:26:15.677 --> 00:26:16.977
is our best shot.

00:26:19.677 --> 00:26:23.447
If you go to my study,
there should be a red notebook.

00:26:23.747 --> 00:26:25.187
That's my research log.

00:26:26.217 --> 00:26:28.317
But I'm pretty sure
the police have already taken it.

00:26:28.617 --> 00:26:29.617
They did?

00:27:40.127 --> 00:27:42.027
"Human Clinical Trial Results."

00:27:42.097 --> 00:27:43.397
(Oh Min Gyu, Male, Batten Disease)

00:27:43.457 --> 00:27:44.467
Batten Disease.

00:27:45.497 --> 00:27:47.067
(Oh Min Gyu, 25 years old,
Recovered Batten disease)

00:28:01.477 --> 00:28:02.477
Hey!

00:28:03.417 --> 00:28:04.417
Stop right there.

00:28:06.687 --> 00:28:07.817
I said stop!

00:28:41.987 --> 00:28:45.087
I'm sorry. I won't do it again.
Please, just let me go.

00:28:46.957 --> 00:28:49.527
Hey everyone, this is legit the place
where Lee Woo Gyeom...

00:28:49.597 --> 00:28:52.627
dismembered his victim. Check this out.

00:28:53.937 --> 00:28:55.367
- Hey.
- The vibe in here is insane, right?

00:28:55.437 --> 00:28:57.967
Is this that "dare challenge"
that's going around?

00:28:58.307 --> 00:29:00.807
Yes. If this video blows up,
I can get ad revenue.

00:29:00.807 --> 00:29:04.307
- And the top guys make over a grand.
- Okay, I get it. Hey, Attorney Park.

00:29:05.007 --> 00:29:08.917
As you know,
we can't guard the scene 24 hours a day.

00:29:08.977 --> 00:29:10.017
And besides,

00:29:10.547 --> 00:29:13.417
this is on the kid who crossed the tape,
right?

00:29:13.487 --> 00:29:14.657
Yes, I'm sorry.

00:29:15.817 --> 00:29:16.817
You.

00:29:18.487 --> 00:29:19.727
Listen to me carefully.

00:29:20.327 --> 00:29:23.257
If you lie, you could be charged
with trespassing and obstructing justice,

00:29:23.427 --> 00:29:24.697
which means up to three years in prison...

00:29:24.967 --> 00:29:26.867
and a fine of up to five grand.
Understand?

00:29:29.967 --> 00:29:31.107
Tell me the truth.

00:29:31.967 --> 00:29:33.067
Did you go inside...

00:29:34.277 --> 00:29:35.637
or not?

00:29:37.077 --> 00:29:38.807
I swear I only filmed nearby.

00:29:38.877 --> 00:29:40.547
Besides, the doors were all locked.

00:29:40.877 --> 00:29:42.977
So you tried the doors, didn't you?

00:29:43.177 --> 00:29:44.947
You can't lie about this.
If you lie, you'll be in huge trouble.

00:29:45.017 --> 00:29:47.287
- You hear me?
- I'm sorry.

00:29:47.987 --> 00:29:49.217
I'm really sorry.

00:29:50.257 --> 00:29:51.427
I'll delete everything, I swear.

00:29:51.487 --> 00:29:52.857
- I'm really...
- Tell me the truth!

00:29:52.927 --> 00:29:53.927
Yes... I opened it.

00:29:54.297 --> 00:29:56.797
(Court)

00:30:05.007 --> 00:30:06.007
You're here early.

00:30:14.617 --> 00:30:15.617
We keep running into each other.

00:30:16.517 --> 00:30:18.447
I thought we were on opposite sides.

00:30:22.387 --> 00:30:24.657
How's Chief Oh doing?

00:30:25.427 --> 00:30:26.427
You mean Chief Oh?

00:30:26.957 --> 00:30:28.427
Back when I was on the bench,

00:30:29.027 --> 00:30:31.097
everyone was in an uproar
about some hothead who had just joined,

00:30:32.567 --> 00:30:34.467
and he told me he was the one
who took you under his wing.

00:30:35.067 --> 00:30:38.607
You mean the troublemaker,
the top student at the Training Institute?

00:30:39.467 --> 00:30:40.977
You should worry less
about other people...

00:30:41.407 --> 00:30:43.077
and more about the murderer
you're defending.

00:30:46.507 --> 00:30:47.517
Hello.

00:30:52.047 --> 00:30:53.147
I know you're all very busy,

00:30:53.747 --> 00:30:55.287
so I appreciate your cooperation.

00:30:56.987 --> 00:30:59.387
The defense witness will be present,

00:31:00.127 --> 00:31:01.797
- correct?
- Yes.

00:31:02.897 --> 00:31:03.897
That is correct.

00:31:05.297 --> 00:31:09.437
At the next hearing,
based on the witnesses' testimonies,

00:31:09.667 --> 00:31:12.367
we'll determine if the crime's motive
was truly to heal people or not.

00:31:12.737 --> 00:31:14.337
We will examine that closely.

00:31:14.537 --> 00:31:15.907
A change in motive...

00:31:16.437 --> 00:31:19.707
- won't change the outcome of this case.
- But the sentencing guidelines...

00:31:20.717 --> 00:31:21.717
could change, though.

00:31:23.117 --> 00:31:24.117
Look,

00:31:25.487 --> 00:31:27.587
he killed 17 people.

00:31:28.887 --> 00:31:30.117
Let's not do this here.

00:31:30.957 --> 00:31:32.157
Save it for the courtroom.

00:31:38.567 --> 00:31:40.327
You saw Reporter Jo's article, didn't you?

00:31:41.067 --> 00:31:42.497
Seemed pretty accurate to me.

00:31:43.497 --> 00:31:45.537
And what part of it is supposedly factual?

00:31:46.507 --> 00:31:47.507
Why?

00:31:48.777 --> 00:31:51.407
If it's not true, then prove it.

00:31:52.077 --> 00:31:54.047
Stop whining about it like a child.

00:31:54.947 --> 00:31:55.947
A child?

00:31:58.287 --> 00:32:02.857
You were my student once.
So you still seem like one to me.

00:32:05.727 --> 00:32:06.857
(Reporter Jo Woo Cheol, Daehan Daily)

00:32:07.087 --> 00:32:09.027
Give my regards to Reporter Jo.

00:32:09.697 --> 00:32:10.697
I'll be on my way.

00:32:10.767 --> 00:32:12.767
(Criminal Court, Civil Petitions Office)

00:32:15.137 --> 00:32:16.137
Hey, Reporter Jo, it's me.

00:32:16.137 --> 00:32:18.867
- Attorney Park, we have a huge problem.
- What?

00:32:19.137 --> 00:32:21.877
They're raiding the office right now!
It's total chaos!

00:32:26.847 --> 00:32:29.217
I'm almost there. I can see the office.
Hang on.

00:32:29.347 --> 00:32:33.957
No, they say my article is defamation,
violates the Comms Network Act,

00:32:34.017 --> 00:32:37.187
and is an obstruction of justice.
Can they really raid an office for this?

00:32:40.357 --> 00:32:44.797
We know you're in there!
Open up before we break the door down!

00:32:51.537 --> 00:32:53.567
They're breaking the door. They broke it!
They're in!

00:32:53.567 --> 00:32:55.537
Please hurry... Hey, wait a minute!
Hold on!

00:32:55.637 --> 00:32:58.207
Hey, what do you think you're doing?
You don't even have a warrant!

00:32:59.177 --> 00:33:00.377
Please cooperate.

00:33:00.677 --> 00:33:02.717
Let's just get this over with
quickly and painlessly.

00:33:03.417 --> 00:33:05.787
Look who it is.
You should've just opened the door.

00:33:06.117 --> 00:33:09.687
- I was on the phone.
- Hey! Hold on a minute!

00:33:10.487 --> 00:33:11.487
Hold on, everyone.

00:33:13.657 --> 00:33:15.697
Let me see the search warrant.

00:33:19.767 --> 00:33:21.367
This is all by the book.

00:33:22.267 --> 00:33:23.897
If we go back to Prosecutor Cha
empty-handed...

00:33:24.937 --> 00:33:26.067
So just step aside, please.

00:33:31.707 --> 00:33:32.707
Go ahead.

00:33:35.147 --> 00:33:37.317
What are you doing here anyway?

00:33:39.917 --> 00:33:41.157
But hold on a second!

00:33:43.517 --> 00:33:44.687
Everyone, just stop for a second.

00:33:46.127 --> 00:33:47.127
I...

00:33:48.227 --> 00:33:51.227
happen to share this office space.

00:33:52.267 --> 00:33:53.527
So anything that belongs to me...

00:33:54.667 --> 00:33:57.197
is absolutely off-limits. Understood?

00:34:01.237 --> 00:34:04.107
Sir, isn't this your desk?

00:34:05.547 --> 00:34:07.477
Your business cards are right here.

00:34:07.847 --> 00:34:08.847
About that...

00:34:11.547 --> 00:34:12.547
I put them in the wrong spot.

00:34:15.117 --> 00:34:17.317
This is my desk right here.

00:34:18.687 --> 00:34:21.497
Yes. That's right.
That's actually my desk.

00:34:21.597 --> 00:34:22.797
Yes, go ahead and take it.

00:34:23.597 --> 00:34:27.667
Sir, you're making this difficult.
This is clear obstruction of justice.

00:34:27.897 --> 00:34:31.167
Fine, then. Take whatever you want.

00:34:31.507 --> 00:34:34.577
But just know I'll be suing you
for larceny...

00:34:34.637 --> 00:34:39.147
for illegally taking my property.
We'll see who has the bigger headache.

00:34:40.007 --> 00:34:41.017
Just you wait.

00:34:46.117 --> 00:34:49.157
Man, what a chaotic day.
I thought I was going to lose my mind.

00:34:50.387 --> 00:34:51.657
That was Prosecutor Cha's doing, right?

00:34:52.357 --> 00:34:54.397
I heard she comes from
a pretty powerful family.

00:34:54.997 --> 00:34:56.497
She's the youngest daughter
of Sejin Group, right?

00:34:56.827 --> 00:34:57.827
That's right.

00:34:58.397 --> 00:35:00.967
So what's the bad blood between you two?

00:35:01.667 --> 00:35:03.537
She was my student back when
I taught at the Training Institute.

00:35:05.107 --> 00:35:06.737
But regardless of her family,

00:35:07.307 --> 00:35:09.907
she was the sharpest student
I ever taught...

00:35:11.547 --> 00:35:12.907
and the biggest pain in my neck.

00:35:13.147 --> 00:35:15.817
Gosh. For a student to be that rude
to her teacher...

00:35:17.917 --> 00:35:21.517
Man, today's been a mess.
When I'm stressed, I like to eat.

00:35:22.187 --> 00:35:25.557
Let's get a drink.
Hey, Min Gyeong! Over here!

00:35:26.487 --> 00:35:27.497
Attorney Park.

00:35:29.527 --> 00:35:31.127
- What's this?
- I invited her.

00:35:33.697 --> 00:35:34.897
Have you been well?

00:35:35.497 --> 00:35:36.997
Yes, I've been fine.

00:35:37.937 --> 00:35:39.007
- It's been a while.
- Yes.

00:35:43.307 --> 00:35:45.607
So, are you really not going
to hire me back?

00:35:47.377 --> 00:35:50.177
CEO Heo said Hae Gang will pay my salary,

00:35:50.277 --> 00:35:52.847
and that it's okay for me
to come and help you.

00:35:53.047 --> 00:35:55.457
Just stay at Hae Gang
and keep doing your job there.

00:35:56.257 --> 00:35:57.257
Attorney Park.

00:35:58.887 --> 00:36:02.327
After you left, I wasn't assigned
to a new supervising attorney,

00:36:02.397 --> 00:36:05.127
so all I do every day is make copies.
This has to be better than that.

00:36:05.667 --> 00:36:07.067
Gosh, what are you talking about?

00:36:11.437 --> 00:36:15.307
Attorney Park.
What if we let Min Gyeong here...

00:36:15.707 --> 00:36:17.337
try to meet with a witness?

00:36:17.707 --> 00:36:18.707
The witnesses?

00:36:19.477 --> 00:36:21.377
You haven't secured a witness yet?

00:36:22.117 --> 00:36:23.647
Not yet.

00:36:23.917 --> 00:36:27.757
Since it's a serial murder case,
most witnesses are reluctant to cooperate.

00:36:31.087 --> 00:36:32.657
Then let me give it a try.

00:36:33.157 --> 00:36:34.157
What?

00:36:34.627 --> 00:36:37.427
I happen to be amazing
at getting people on board.

00:36:38.427 --> 00:36:39.897
For example, at my college festival,

00:36:40.127 --> 00:36:43.897
I set up all the lonely students
on group dates,

00:36:44.167 --> 00:36:47.637
and our pop-up bar broke the all-time
school sales record. That was all me.

00:36:50.337 --> 00:36:51.577
But...

00:36:52.007 --> 00:36:55.847
- Recruiting a witness isn't exactly...
- You don't need a certificate for that.

00:36:56.477 --> 00:36:59.547
I don't have a certificate,
but I do have confidence.

00:37:00.347 --> 00:37:04.787
Maybe it's because
we're a couple of dreary faces...

00:37:05.027 --> 00:37:06.787
that it hasn't been working out.

00:37:07.387 --> 00:37:08.927
I know I can do a really good job.

00:37:09.557 --> 00:37:10.557
Please?

00:37:13.327 --> 00:37:15.967
For crying out loud.
What's gotten into you two?

00:37:17.437 --> 00:37:18.767
All right, fine. Then...

00:37:19.207 --> 00:37:23.737
Min Gyeong has no field experience,
so Reporter Jo, show her the ropes.

00:37:23.937 --> 00:37:26.147
Of course. That's my specialty.

00:37:27.307 --> 00:37:29.977
Min Gyeong, looking forward to working
with you. I'm Jo Woo Cheol.

00:37:30.047 --> 00:37:31.487
Hey, I'm just going to speak casually.

00:37:32.117 --> 00:37:33.847
Since you decided
to speak informally first,

00:37:34.787 --> 00:37:35.917
I'll do the same.

00:37:36.817 --> 00:37:39.487
- What?
- I'm just kidding, sir.

00:37:40.357 --> 00:37:43.357
- Well, then, shall we have a drink?
- All right.

00:37:43.627 --> 00:37:45.497
- All right, glasses up.
- Yes.

00:37:45.567 --> 00:37:47.637
- Cheers.
- Good.

00:37:50.737 --> 00:37:53.007
Lee Woo Gyeom will surely pay
for his crimes, right?

00:37:54.137 --> 00:37:56.607
But if it's true that he really cured
an incurable disease...

00:37:57.337 --> 00:37:59.347
so that he can help even more people,

00:37:59.647 --> 00:38:01.177
we have to at least give it a shot,
