He stood up?

00:43:45.227 --> 00:43:46.727
So that everyone
in this court can hear you,

00:43:48.427 --> 00:43:50.127
please say that again...

00:43:51.057 --> 00:43:52.167
in a loud, clear voice.

00:43:53.497 --> 00:43:54.497
Yes.

00:43:55.437 --> 00:43:56.597
He stood up!

00:44:02.977 --> 00:44:04.207
Could you describe that moment...

00:44:05.847 --> 00:44:07.547
in more detail?

00:44:08.777 --> 00:44:11.447
"Mom! Mom, look at this!"

00:44:12.687 --> 00:44:14.387
That's what he shouted.

00:44:15.217 --> 00:44:18.887
I was shocked and rushed to his room,
and when I got there,

00:44:20.587 --> 00:44:22.797
he was standing on his own two feet.

00:44:25.627 --> 00:44:26.797
That's right.

00:44:27.097 --> 00:44:30.067
Not once in 18 years.

00:44:30.567 --> 00:44:32.467
Sang Woo, who could never stand,

00:44:32.467 --> 00:44:35.537
was standing there,
completely on his own,

00:44:36.037 --> 00:44:38.807
right there in front of the witness.

00:44:39.847 --> 00:44:41.107
Witness,

00:44:41.717 --> 00:44:43.077
that is the truth, is it not?

00:44:43.717 --> 00:44:44.717
Yes.

00:44:45.317 --> 00:44:48.187
- He was standing all on his own.
- And after that,

00:44:48.957 --> 00:44:52.557
did Sang Woo's condition get worse,
or did it not?

00:44:52.787 --> 00:44:53.987
It did not.

00:44:54.487 --> 00:44:56.627
It was as if Sang Woo
had been given a new life.

00:44:57.297 --> 00:44:59.367
He told me how incredibly grateful he was
to Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom.

00:45:01.667 --> 00:45:03.197
He asked me to be sure to tell him that.

00:45:11.407 --> 00:45:12.477
Thank you.

